{"lemma":"فَظِّ","slug":"فَظِّ","root":"ف.ظ.ظ","root_slug":"ف-ظ-ظ","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ظ-ظ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَظّ","root":"فظظ","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34181","n34182"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B8%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be rude"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rude","examples":[{"text":"وَلَوْ كُنْتَ فَظًّا غَلِيظَ الْقَلْبِ لَٱنْفَضُّوا مِنْ حَوْلِكَ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"walrus"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/faðˤðˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34181","headword_ar":"فَظَّ","root":"fZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZiZota","text_ar":"فَظِظْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZaAZapN","text_ar":"فَظَاظَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZaZN","text_ar":"فَظَظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) but the former is the more common because of the difficulty of pronouncing the doubled letter in the latter, (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiZaAZN","text_ar":"فِظَاظٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with these, (M, K,) and so is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZaAZN","text_ar":"فَظَاظٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but these two are simple substs., (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZ~N","text_ar":"فَظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough, coarse, rude,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., as expl. below]; (S, M, Msb, K; *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to be unduly feared."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZ~apu","text_ar":"فَظَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2419},{"kind":"text","text":"aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZ~N","text_ar":"فَظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TK;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AftZ~hu","text_ar":"افتظّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He let it out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely the water termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZ~N","text_ar":"فَظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by cutting open the stomach"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a camel]: (M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he pressed it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"squeezed it, out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely the water so termed, (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the stomach,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and drank it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kari$a baEiyrK","text_ar":"كَرِشَ بَعِيرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AftZ~","text_ar":"افتظّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he slaughtered a camel, and pressed out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"squeezed out, the water of its stomach, and strained it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Esh-Sháfi'ee, T:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AftZ~","text_ar":"افتظّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he gave his camel to drink, then bound his mouth in order that he might not ruminate, and, when attacked by thirst, cut open his belly, and pressed out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"squeezed out, the fluid of the feces of his stomach, and drank it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkari$a","text_ar":"الكَرِشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoZaZotu","text_ar":"اَفْظَظْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I pressed out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"squeezed out, the water of the stomach."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","M","K","TA","TK"]},{"entry_id":"n34182","headword_ar":"فَظٌّ","root":"fZ","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a man, (T, S, M, &c.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rough; coarse; rude; unkind; hard; churlish; uncivil; surly; hard to deal with; incompliant; unobsequious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K, and Bd in iii. 153;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil in disposition; illnatured;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, and Bd and Jel ubi suprà;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard-hearted; hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe; rough, coarse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, so as to be unduly feared;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse, in speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"austere, therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth:) [said in the T to be from the same word in the sense next following; but accord. to the M, the reverse seems to be the case:] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoZaAZN","text_ar":"اَفْظَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lafaZ~N baZ~N","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَفَظٌّ بَظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is rough, coarse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; the latter word being an imitative sequent; (M, K;) as such we regard it because Th, who mentions it, does not explan it; (M;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faZiyZN","text_ar":"فَظِيظٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baZiyZN","text_ar":"بَظِيظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. signifies the same]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bZ","text_ar":"بظ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water of the stomach"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (T, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is pressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"squeezed, out, and drunk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on an occasion of want of water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the waterless deserts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water that comes forth from the stomach"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because it is a coarse, or bitter, beverage: (M:) it may not be used for the purpose of religious purification: (Esh-Sháfi'ee, T:) also, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"urine of horses which is drunk on an occasion of thirst:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuZuwZN","text_ar":"فُظُوظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus used by Mutemmem Ibn-Nuweyreh. (M, L.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","T","S","K","M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}